Plasma displayed postivity. Most normal tissues showed weak to moderate nuclear positivity. Purkinje cells exhibited strong immunoreactivity. Skin, lymphoid tissues, breast, liver, glial cells and soft tissues were in general negative.
Most malignant tissues showed weak to moderate nuclear positivity. Malignant lymphomas and renal cell carcinomas were negative.
